{
  "text": "Yet another domain of permissive conditions is the absence of violence and armed conflict. We use three indicators. Internal peace is the inverse of Gibney et al.'s (2010) ''political terror scale,'' measuring the absence of state repression. External peace is the inverse of a society's international conflict involvement, taken from [CITATION_1] . 10 Alternatively, we used the ''good governance'' indicators from the World Bank (Kaufman et al. 2010) . But these indicators show no closer association with emancipative values than do the indicators of the Risk Guide. 11 We experimented with different prevalence measures, using the median instead of the mean or the geometric and quadratic means instead of the arithmetic means as well as proportions of respondents scoring in the upper quartiles and quintiles of our multi-point value measures. None of these variants produced stronger results than those obtained by the arithmetic population means. For a discussion of the appropriateness of aggregating individual-level values to the society level, see the Response Section in OA 23 (pp. 39-41).",
  "citation_candidates": [
